  "prompt": "What should you do if you're losing your voice?",
  "response": "If you're losing your voice, here are some helpful tips:\n\n1. Rest your voice\n- Avoid talking as much as possible\n- Don't whisper (which can strain your vocal cords)\n- Speak softly and minimally\n\n2. Stay hydrated\n- Drink plenty of water\n- Avoid caffeine and alcohol\n- Use warm herbal tea with honey\n\n3. Soothe your throat\n- Gargle with warm salt water\n- Use throat lozenges\n- Try honey to coat and calm your throat\n\n4. Humidify the air\n- Use a humidifier\n- Take steamy showers\n- Keep your environment moist\n\n5. Avoid irritants\n- Don't smoke\n- Stay away from secondhand smoke\n- Limit exposure to harsh chemicals or dust\n\n6. Support your immune system\n- Get plenty of rest\n- Eat nutritious foods\n- Consider vitamin supplements\n\n7. Treat underlying conditions\n- If voice loss is due to a cold or infection, treat it appropriately\n- Use over-the-counter medications if needed\n\n8. See a doctor if\n- Voice loss persists more than 2 weeks\n- You have difficulty breathing\n- You have a fever or severe pain",
